    <item>
      <title>Re: Fetching a node's tags from multiple attrib...</title>
      <link>http://projects.ez.no/eztags/forum/general/fetching_a_node_s_tags_from_multiple_attributes/re_fetching_a_node_s_tags_from_multiple_attrib</link>
      <description>Hi Hayden,&#13;
&#13;
there's no ready made fetch that would list all the tags from all attributes, but you can always do something like this:&#13;
&#13;
&lt;code&gt;&#13;
{foreach $node.data_map as $attribute}&#13;
    {if $attribute.data_type_string|eq( 'eztags' )}&#13;
        {if $attribute.has_content}&#13;
            {attribute_view_gui attribute=$attribute}&#13;
        {/if}&#13;
    {/if}&#13;
{/foreach}&#13;
&lt;/code&gt;&#13;
&#13;
I hope that's enough :)</description>
      <author>community@ez.no (Edi Modrić)</author>
